Good question Venky ğŸ‘Œ
Since youâ€™re backend-focused, Iâ€™ll explain React build process in a **very simple backend-style thinking**.

---

# ğŸ§  First Understand This

When you run:

```
npm start
```

React runs in **development mode**.

When you run:

```
npm run build
```

React creates a **production-ready optimized version**.

That process is called **Build Process**.

---

# ğŸ”„ Think Like This (Backend Example)

In Spring Boot:

* You write Java code
* Then you create a `.jar` file
* Then you deploy that `.jar`

React is similar.

* You write React code (JSX)
* Then it converts everything into optimized HTML + CSS + JS
* Then you deploy that

---

# ğŸ“¦ What Happens During `npm run build`?

## Step 1ï¸âƒ£ JSX â†’ JavaScript

You write:

```jsx
<h1>Hello</h1>
```

Browser doesnâ€™t understand JSX.

Build process converts it into:

```js
React.createElement("h1", null, "Hello")
```

This is done by **Babel**.

---

## Step 2ï¸âƒ£ Combine All Files

React app has:

* Many JS files
* Many CSS files
* Many images

Build process:

* Combines files
* Removes unused code
* Minifies code (removes spaces & comments)

Example:

Before:

```js
function add(a, b) {
   return a + b;
}
```

After build:

```js
function a(b,c){return b+c}
```

Smaller file = faster loading.

---

## Step 3ï¸âƒ£ Create Static Folder

After build, you get:

```
build/
   index.html
   static/
       js/
       css/
```

This is just static files.

Now your backend (Spring Boot or Nginx) can serve it.

---

# ğŸš€ Why Build Is Important?

Development mode:

* Big files
* Slow
* Debug-friendly

Production build:

* Small
* Fast
* Secure
* Optimized

You should NEVER deploy development mode.

---

# ğŸ”¥ Real Example (Your CMARF Project)

If you connect React + Spring Boot:

Frontend:

```
npm run build
```

Then copy `build/` files into:

```
src/main/resources/static
```

Now Spring Boot serves frontend + backend together.

Thatâ€™s how real production works.

---

# ğŸ¯ Simple One-Line Definition

> React build process converts developer-friendly code into browser-friendly optimized code.

